Certainly, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "smetati" in different forms and positions, with a star (*) indicating the word itself. English translations are provided in parentheses:

1. *Smeta mi* ovaj buka u restoranu. (I am bothered by this noise in the restaurant.)
2. Da li ti *smetaju* moje cipele? (Do my shoes bother you?)
3. Ona *ne smeta* nikome u ovoj sobi. (She doesn't bother anyone in this room.)
4. *Smeta li vam* ako otvorim prozor? (Does it bother you if I open the window?)
5. Njima *smetaju* zvukovi iz susedne kuće. (They are bothered by the sounds coming from the neighboring house.)
6. Da li vam *smeta* dim cigarete? (Does cigarette smoke bother you?)
7. Molim vas, *ne smetajte* mi dok radim. (Please, don't bother me while I'm working.)
8. Deca *smetaju* roditeljima tokom video sastanka. (Children bother parents during a video conference.)
9. Njemu *smeta* kada ga prekidaju. (He is bothered when he is interrupted.)
10. *Smetaće nam* ova kiša na putu do tamo. (This rain will bother us on the way there.)